Python implementation of the Local Binary Pattern Histogram algorithm for facial recognition.

Run the "LBPH_train.py" file first, then run the "LBPH_main.py"

Cambridge ORL database: 40 subjects, 10 photos each.

20 of the subjects are chosen as the known subjects. 

4 photos each of the known subjects and unknown subjects are used for training.

Testing faces are drawn from the remaining 240 photos (6 each of the total 40 subjects)

Current specific tuning results in 90% precision over 100 random test cases
